It is clear that unidirectional metasurface supports polarization conversion from linear to cross polarized or circularly polarized reflected fields. As shown in schematic design illustration of Fig. 2 the rotation of the outer rings to form supercell with multidirectional splits can induce interesting resonant absorption phenomenon. The rotation allows induced currents to cancel each other and therefore minimize the radiated far field scattering (anti-reflection characteristics). Figure 4a shows that the magnitude of co- and cross- field components reflected field component reduce to -10 dB. The reason behind this resonant absorption is the destructive interference of induced currents on metasurface elements. Figure 4b shows that the absorptivity remains larger than >90%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
